book.part:
		Cache



				Cache Service is developed based on OSCache, 
				and is a service which caches object that can share conditions. 
				Objects that do not change often but are used frequently and incur high cost to create, 
				can benefit as the following by using Cache.




There is no need to fetch frequently accessed data from database every time, so there is less overhead.




Memory can be used efficiently because object is not created every time.



